Title: PARKING BRAKE: PARKING BRAKE CABLE (for Rear Side): REMOVAL; 2018 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2017 -        ]

REMOVAL

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

The necessary procedures (adjustment, calibration, initialization, or registration) that must be performed after parts are removed and installed, or replaced during No. 3 parking brake cable assembly removal/installation are shown below.

Necessary Procedures After Parts Removed/Installed/Replaced

Replaced Part or Performed Procedure

Necessary Procedure

Effect/Inoperative Function when Necessary Procedure not Performed

Link

  • Replacement of heated oxygen sensor
  • Gas leak from exhaust system is repaired

Inspection after repair

  • Poor idle, etc.
  • Engine start function, etc.

CAUTION:

To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust pipe or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the No. 2 parking brake cable assembly and No. 3 parking brake cable assembly.

PROCEDURE

1. LOOSEN NO. 1 WIRE ADJUSTING NUT

Click here

2. REMOVE REAR CONSOLE BOX ASSEMBLY

Click here

3. SEPARATE NO. 1 PARKING BRAKE CABLE ASSEMBLY

Click here

4. SEPARATE NO. 1 PARKING BRAKE PULL ROD SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Separate the No. 1 parking brake pull rod sub-assembly from the No. 3 parking brake cable assembly as shown in the illustration.

5. REMOVE FRONT EXHAUST PIPE ASSEMBLY (TWC: Rear Catalyst)

Click here

6. REMOVE FRONT NO. 2 FLOOR HEAT INSULATOR

(a) Remove the 4 nuts and front No. 2 floor heat insulator.

7. REMOVE REAR FLOOR SIDE MEMBER COVER LH (for LH Side)

Click here

8. REMOVE NO. 1 FLOOR UNDER COVER ASSEMBLY (for RH Side)

Click here

9. REMOVE PARKING BRAKE LEVER PROTECTOR

(a) Remove the parking brake lever protector from the No. 3 parking brake cable assembly.

10. REMOVE NO. 3 PARKING BRAKE CABLE ASSEMBLY

(a) Remove the 4 bolts and nut, and separate the No. 3 parking brake cable assembly.

(b) Pull out the No. 3 parking brake cable assembly to the outside of the vehicle body.

(c) Separate the No. 3 parking brake cable assembly from the rear disc brake cylinder assembly.

(d) Disengage the clip and remove the No. 3 parking brake cable assembly.
